claim.claim-text:
An optical information reading method, comprising the steps of:
a step of adding n element widths (n ≥ 2) containing adjacent bar and space in one character to obtain respective 2- through n-element added widths;
a step of converting each of the obtained 2- through n-element added widths into a module number with respect to one character to obtain the module number of the 2- through n-element added widths;
a step of extracting a candidate character by narrowing down the target characters wherein each module number of the obtained 2- through n-element added widths is an integer with an error equal to or less than 1; and
a step of comparing the extracted candidate character having the module numbers of the 2-through n-element added widths with an expected value character for evaluating the candidate character to search for an expected value character having the strongest correlation to the candidate character.
